posts.name: Jason Daming
posts.cooked: Did you download the latest version of LabVIEW (2021 SP1) or the currently support FRC version of LabVIEW found here ?  There are multiple modules that are required to run FRC LabVIEW code beyond what might just be installed with a “normal” LabVIEW install.

posts.name: Mark McLeod
posts.cooked: I suspect interference between 2021 and 2020 components. The safest approach is to uninstall all the LV products, both LV 2021 and 2020, and everything else listed in the NI Package Manager, then reinstall just the FRC 2020 SP1 version & the Game Tools.

posts.name: Mark McLeod
posts.cooked:
The step-by-steps are here: Installing LabVIEW for FRC (LabVIEW only) — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation

I think you should be able to just run the install again and the installer will pick up on things that are missing.

Things to be wary of:

Don’t check or uncheck anything from any of the lists that popup during the process. Not all items on the lists are checked, so stay away from the Select All buttons, too.

Say “No” to the NI Update Service offer. That would install stuff that hasn’t been vetted for FRC. LV Install 5 862×187 22.3 KB

LV Install 5 862×187 22.3 KB

LV Install 5 862×187 22.3 KB

Keep an eye out for any error messages that popup during the install. It looks like your install errored out in the middle of the process. I have encountered errors on some installs and was able to work around them.
